fields.description:
Todd at Somo Audience/IZON Network noted that the high fraud that Native Ads is recording is the same issue that the Pixalate team has been investigating and is working on solution involving ad quality scans, noted in the ticket below:  
https://pixalate.atlassian.net/browse/CS-3151

The report from Todd -Nativeads_IZON_PixalaterEPORT - is where he mentions a correlation between increased unique creatives(CRIDS) sent on 8-10 and increase in IVT.  If you review the 3rd tab in the attached excel doc you will notice IVT increases with an increase in CRIDS, increase in scans by Somo , TMT and IP mismatch.   Todd feels that this all points to the ad quality audit issue.

Todd mentions to Ron at Native Ads that IZON is not counting 1st and 3rd party audits and is also passing audit as the win macro.  Although IZON and Native Ads are not counting and are filtering out the AQ Audits/scans from our reporting, Pixalate is not. 

Both accounts have given me permission to review data from both dashboards, and then start working on the best way to show audits in Pixalate reports.  

Somo Audience/IZON - sa
Native Ads - nad

Somo Audience/IZON - Native Ads Advertiser ID = 636
Native Ads - IZON Publisher ID = 36269

I pulled MtD reports for both dashboards, attached, and noticed the following:
IVT by Day - significant IVT increase on 8/8, then decrease on 8/9, the increases again 8/10, and as impressions decrease, so does IVT.

IVT by Fraud Type - for Native Ads, top 2 fraud types are:
Display impression fraud
Hijacked session

For Somo Audience/IZON, top 3 fraud types are:
Display impression fraud
Duplicate impressions
Hijacked session

Todd mentions IP mismatch, as the cause, but can you confirm this?

IVT by AppID - both Somo Audience and Native Ads have the same top 3 AppIDs:
1207472156
1413942319
com.europosit.pixelcoloring

IVT by Domain - 2 of the same domains were in the top 3
inner-active.com
mopub.com

Please note that I have already relayed the AQ/creative scanning proposed solution provided by [~accountid:5ca29e4461c2276e1bd4fc59] for the Somo Audience/EngageBDR issue, and once you relay any additional findings/insights, I can reiterate this to the team again but want to make sure we address the IP mismatch correlation and false positive IVT trends Todd is referring to in his report.

Please review, and if you have any questions or need anything else concerning this request, please do not hesitate to reach out.
fields.summary: Somo Audience - False/Positive IVT issue Native Ads is experiencing with IZON (formerly Somo)
